                "html": "<p>For <i>intravenous infusion</i> (<i>Penbritin</i>\n<tm tmtype=\"reg\"/>), give intermittently <i>in</i> Glucose 5% <i>or</i> Sodium chloride 0.9%. Reconstituted solutions diluted and given without delay; suggested volume 100&#8239;mL given over 30&#8211;60 minutes</p><p>\n<i>via</i> drip tubing <i>in</i> Glucose 5% <i>or</i> Sodium chloride 0.9%. Continuous infusion not usually recommended.</p>"
            }
        ]
    },
